subSubSection.paragraph:
Sensory canals and pores.
Sensory canals with nasal pore close to each posterior nostril, no anterior interorbital pore, single posterior interorbital pore, no postorbital pore, long slit-like pore behind eye (this canal and elongate pore is supported by sphenotic bone); two additional pores in oculoscapular canal over preopercle and two pores in short canal over opercle; three preopercular pores present (
Fig. 12
). Sensory papillae in longitudinal pattern (
Fig. 12
).
